WEBVTT



00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:11.872
Happy Fat Tuesday. this is the Gospel of Matthew podcast from Perdido Bay Methodist Church.

00:00:11.584 --> 00:00:16.928
And today is Tuesday, February the 17th, and our passage is Matthew 15, verses 1 through 12.

00:00:16.736 --> 00:00:18.624
10 verses 1 through 20.

00:00:19.008 --> 00:00:20.672
In this passage,

00:00:20.512 --> 00:00:25.600
And we see what we have as known as the vice list from Jesus.

00:00:25.504 --> 00:00:28.928
19.

00:00:29.504 --> 00:00:32.896
People like to consider the grace of

00:00:32.672 --> 00:00:36.160
Of Jesus the forgiveness of Jesus

00:00:36.096 --> 00:00:38.336
The kindness of Jesus.

00:00:38.432 --> 00:00:40.416
And all of these are

00:00:40.416 --> 00:00:44.224
Qualities which we must embrace and give thanks for.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:52.608
But out of this emerges what Jesus gives us in the vice list. it is because of his grace, because of his mercy.

00:00:52.448 --> 00:00:55.680
Because of his great care for us.

00:00:55.424 --> 00:00:58.336
That he tells us the things that will destroy.

00:00:58.240 --> 00:01:02.496
"'He tells us the things that are out of bounds "'for those who are followers of him.'"

00:01:03.104 --> 00:01:04.160
People,

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:09.600
I don't like to consider that Jesus draws a firm boundary in things that are difficult.

00:01:09.344 --> 00:01:13.344
acceptable as followers of Jesus and things that are unacceptable.

00:01:13.248 --> 00:01:17.632
There are limitations to the freedom that Christians have.

00:01:17.984 --> 00:01:22.208
We are not forgiven of sin that we might that we may continue to persevere in sin

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:26.944
That we might willingly do the things that violate the will and the heart of God.

00:01:27.072 --> 00:01:31.648
And Jesus tells us that it is in our heart where these things emerge.

00:01:31.616 --> 00:01:37.536
Out of our heart emerged things that manifest in our hands, in our words, and in our actions.

00:01:37.632 --> 00:01:41.568
"'If our heart is impure, our actions and our words will be also.'"

00:01:41.664 --> 00:01:43.648
If our heart is pure

00:01:43.456 --> 00:01:44.864
That also

00:01:44.608 --> 00:01:48.416
It must be seen in our words and our thoughts today.

00:01:48.384 --> 00:01:50.016
And in our actions

00:01:50.752 --> 00:01:55.040
This is not mere morality. This is transformation.

00:01:54.976 --> 00:01:57.504
Our heart must be transformed

00:01:57.280 --> 00:01:59.840
By the holy spirit of god

00:01:59.904 --> 00:02:04.512
When the Holy Spirit dwells within us, it leaves no place for things like slander or

00:02:04.224 --> 00:02:08.480
False testimony, immorality, murdering, adultery,

00:02:08.736 --> 00:02:10.304
These things,

00:02:10.048 --> 00:02:12.416
Are moved out of the house.

00:02:12.288 --> 00:02:14.432
Because when God dwells,

00:02:14.208 --> 00:02:18.688
It leaves no space for things that are of darkness.

00:02:19.776 --> 00:02:23.520
As we consider chapter 15, specifically these verses, it says,

00:02:23.264 --> 00:02:24.832
1 through 20.

00:02:24.960 --> 00:02:28.832
Let us think about the seriousness with which Jesus died for.

00:02:28.896 --> 00:02:32.704
Jesus died that we might be forgiven of sin.

00:02:32.704 --> 00:02:36.992
But also that we might no longer be mastered by sin.

00:02:37.056 --> 00:02:44.000
That we would trust in him to cleanse us, to purify us, to shape us into his image.

00:02:43.904 --> 00:02:45.376
His life,

00:02:45.280 --> 00:02:48.064
His example, his will,

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:49.216
His way.

00:02:49.280 --> 00:02:52.896
For he is the way, the truth, and the life.

00:02:53.056 --> 00:02:56.576
And he tells us things that cannot be of the life,

00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:59.008
I'm a follower of Jesus Christ. Amen.

00:02:59.264 --> 00:03:00.960
Consider our heart.

00:03:00.832 --> 00:03:02.464
What are we listening to?

00:03:02.368 --> 00:03:03.904
What are we watching?

00:03:04.096 --> 00:03:06.720
Who are we allowing to speak into our life?

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:11.264
Are we going first to the scripture or first to something else?

00:03:11.296 --> 00:03:13.536
We must be going first to the scripture.

00:03:13.376 --> 00:03:17.088
First to God, first in prayer, seeking his will,

00:03:16.992 --> 00:03:19.104
Seeking his reign in our heart.

00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:25.952
And out of this will flow everything else that Jesus has for us, things that do not defile, the things that enrich.

00:03:25.632 --> 00:03:28.768
and show the abundance of life that God gives us.

00:03:28.672 --> 00:03:30.400
In Jesus Christ.

00:03:30.720 --> 00:03:34.624
Our producer for today's podcast is Kenny Stewart. Thank you.
